^{14, 15}$, which constrains conventional geometries at cryogenic\noperation$^6$. Finally, the reduced physical area of the device and its\nincreased responsivity allows us, for the first time, to take advantage of the\nintrinsic high frequency response of the quantum detector$^7$ at room\ntemperature. By beating two quantum cascade lasers$^{16}$ we have measured the\nheterodyne signal at high frequencies up to 4 GHz.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Sep 2017 17:06:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-08"}
